<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP20_AdventureAwaits_Getaways" s="481192">
  <T n="category">481599<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_AdventureAwaits--></T>
  <T n="name">0x1B27A70D<!--String: "Getaway Experience"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_Getaways_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:0804f4a9e80c36f2</T>
      <T n="text">0x38B8BA8A<!--String: "In Live Mode, there is a compact schedule panel in the top left whenever a Getaway is active. This gives you a quick overview of what's happening now and what's coming up next. Use it to keep tabs on the day's activities without diving into the planner!\n\nNeed more details? Select the dropdown arrow to expand the full schedule. You'll see a breakdown of each role's assigned activity for the current timeslot. Whether your Sim is the Camp Chef, Love Interest, or Nature Explorer, you'll know exactly what they're supposed to be doing. These activities help drive the narrative, but they aren't Events with Goals, there's no checklist to complete. Just enjoy the story as it unfolds!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_Getaways_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:0804f4a9e80c36f1</T>
      <T n="text">0x5318A269<!--String: "Want to extend the fun, or cancel the Getaway? Select the “X” button at the top of the schedule to either extend your Getaway or end it early.\n\nJust make sure your household has enough Simoleons to cover the cost after extending. If not, your Sims may be forced to leave the Getaway early!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_Getaways_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:0804f4a9e80c36f0</T>
      <T n="text">0xF923B150<!--String: "When an <font color="#199C2C"><b>Elimination Rule</b></font> is active, one Sim will be eliminated each day at a fixed time. For Player Choice Elimination, you'll be prompted to choose which Sim leaves, so each day becomes a critical decision point.\n\nOnly one elimination happens per day, and the elimination sequence continues until a single Sim remains. However, if your Getaway duration ends early before all eliminations are complete, the Getaway will still wrap up without naming the final winner. To see the challenge through to the end, make sure to set enough days upfront or Extend the Getaway as needed!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_Getaways_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:0804f4a9e80c36f7</T>
      <T n="text">0x9BC83908<!--String: "If your household Sim gets eliminated during a Getaway, you'll be given a choice to end the Getaway immediately, or reassign your household Sim into a different role to watch the rest unfold from the sidelines.\n\nWhether you're calling the shots or watching the chaos, the call is yours!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_Getaways_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:0804f4a9e80c36f6</T>
      <T n="text">0xF2EBA7A2<!--String: "Every Getaway offers a chance for Sims to come back with rewards, memories, and maybe even a new side of themselves.\n\nIf your Getaway includes any active Rules, Sims who stick it out to the end will earn themed rewards tied to those rules. These can include things like collectibles, potions, Simoleons, or reward traits!\n\nAs Sims participate in scheduled main activities, they build progress toward different activity categories, such as Outdoor, Social, or Hobbies. By the end of the Getaway, the category they engaged with most may award them a special Reward Trait with lasting benefits, like faster Skill gains!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_Getaways_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:0804f4a9e80c36f5</T>
      <T n="text">0x88F0C8D0<!--String: "From the first activity to the final elimination, you've set the schedule, assigned the roles, and chosen the rules!\n\nWhether your Sim walks away with rewards, rivalries, romances, or regrets, one thing's for sure: no two Getaways play out the same. So when you're ready...plan your next Getaway and let the adventure begin!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_EP20_AdventureAwaits</E>
  </L>
  <T n="ui_sort_order">12</T>
</I>